The Brazilian Coffee Institute(IBC) could close May export registrations tonight followingextremely heavy sales today, exporters said.    They estimated registrations today at between 1.0 mln and1.2 mln 60 kilo bags. Yesterday 645,000 bags were registered.    The exporters said over 1.0 mln bags of total registrationscould have been the declaration of sales made in the six weeksduring which books were closed. The rest would be new sales.    When the IBC opened May registrations from yesterday it didnot set any volume limit. April registrations opened and closedon February 16 when a daily record 1.68 mln bags were declared. Reuter&#3;